{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"343f5541-1f36-44c5-a499-679b5a0471bd","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) doesn't work with MTP. Use the MTP `--filter` instead:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **`&`** → **`and`** (logical operator is a word, not a symbol)\n- `|` → `or`, `!` → `not`\n- The `~` (contains) operator still works\n\n### 2. `[Trait]` → `[Category]` for the `Category` filter\n\nIn xUnit v3, `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` should be replaced with the first-class `[Category(\"Smoke\")]` attribute (from `Xunit.v3`). Your current `[Trait]` may still work for filtering, but the idiomatic v3 way is:\n\n```csharp\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]\n```\n\nWant me to apply both changes to your files?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c56e12b-e232-4537-ba08-bfabf9bb8c09","outputTokens":271,"requestId":"5C2E:23477B:CD472:100D7E:69F54C19"},"id":"fbb8d5c9-a72c-4fb2-94b0-3c22972408b6","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:58:09.417Z","parentId":"be4f09da-1c41-4205-bdff-64baab8e2dbf"}
